    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Resort Policies</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Janet Gerske letter expresses shock that Sandals resort would declare its anti-homosexual policies in May 28 letter to editor (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I was shocked that Sandals resort would declare its antihomosexual policies in a letter to the editor (May 28). Would the management trumpet race discrimination with as little apparent concern? I doubt it. I hope that honeymooners will choose not to start their marriages in such an environment.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: I was shocked that Sandals resort would declare its antihomosexual policies in a letter to the editor (May 28). Would the management trumpet race discrimination with as little apparent concern? I doubt it. I hope that honeymooners will choose not to start their marriages in such an environment.</p>
        <p>It's one thing to exclude children: they grow up. Nudists can put on clothes. Excluding people by immutable sexual orientation is unacceptable.</p>
        <p>JANET GERSKE  Chicago</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
